ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Untitled-design-12.jpg
CATEGORIES:Collections programming,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260717T115540Z
DESCRIPTION:Sonic Coins\, is a listening session that explores the material\, historical\, and sonic lives of coins from the museum's collection\, featuring a sound work created through research and cataloguing\, using the textures\, clinks\, and resonances of the coins to imagine a unique sonic archive.\n\nSpanning histories of trade\, cultural exchange\, modernity\, and colonial rule\, the selected coins invite new ways of engaging with objects and their journeys. The session\, with Shravani Upadhyay from the MAP team\, concludes with a viewing of the featured coins and a conversation about their histories and significance within the collection.
DTEND:20260721T113000Z
DTSTART:20260721T103000Z
SUMMARY:Sonic Coins
UID:1350@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/sonic-coins/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/Screenshot-2026-07-15-204308.png
CATEGORIES:Guided Walk,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260716T125428Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credit: Arun Prasad's Comic Archive\nJoin us for a special Indian Sign Language-interpreted\, Deaf-led guided walk of A Moving Line.\n\nLed by Akanksha Kambale from the MAP team\, this session centres on Deaf perspectives\, with Indian Sign Language (ISL) as the primary language of engagement\, offering a visual-first\, inclusive approach to experiencing the exhibition.\n\nThis programme is part of the celebration of the opening of A Moving Line: 1500 Years of Indian Visual Storytelling. 
DTEND:20260726T113000Z
DTSTART:20260726T103000Z
