BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/2-e1784209220254.jpg
CATEGORIES:Lecture-Demonstration,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260716T134544Z
DESCRIPTION:Image Credits: Tholpavakoothu Sangam\nTholpavakoothu is Kerala's ancient ritual leather shadow puppetry.  Artist Vipin Viswanatha Pulavar and his team from Tholpavakoothu Sangam present a lecture-demonstration introducing the history\, traditions\, cultural significance\, techniques\, and contemporary relevance of Tholpavakoothu. \n\nThe session includes traditional and contemporary adaptations of the performance\, a display of authentic leather puppets\, explaining their craftsmanship\, materials\, symbolism\, and the process of making and preserving them. You would also get to experience the traditional style of recitation\, including selected verses\, narration\, and vocal techniques used in Tholpavakoothu performances\, alongside an introduction to the traditional musical accompaniment and the role of rhythm\, storytelling\, and ritual elements in the performance.\n\nThis programme is part of the celebration of the opening of A Moving Line: 1500 Years of Indian Visual Storytelling. 
DTEND:20260726T140000Z
DTSTART:20260726T130000Z
SUMMARY:Tholpavakoothu Lecture-Demonstration
UID:1341@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/tholpavakoothu-lecture-demonstration/
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://map-india.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/07/PTG.01534-1-scaled.jpg
CATEGORIES:Panel Discussion,MAP,CBD
DTSTAMP:20260717T100000Z
DESCRIPTION:How does the world of comic-making function? This panel discussion focuses on the landscape of comic-making\, funding and revenue models for comic art\, and what authorship looks like in the times of emerging technologies like AI. Director of CIBDI Vincent Eches\, Indian artist Pinaki De and journalist/editor/cultural commentator Sonia Dechamps join this discussion moderated by Karthika VK\, Publisher\, Westland Books. This session brings to light the contemporary scenarios in both French and Indian perspectives.\n\nThis programme is part of the celebration of the opening of A Moving Line: 1500 Years of Indian Visual Storytelling.
DTEND:20260726T120000Z
DTSTART:20260726T110000Z
SUMMARY:Infrastructures of Comic-making
UID:1349@map-india.org
URL:https://map-india.org/map-events/infrastructures-of-comic-making/
END:VEVENT
